  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Buckets of Dignity: Life-Saving Humanitarian Action and Health Wellbeing for Rohingya Refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The health post will provide regular Out-Patient Department (OPD) including ENT services with outpatient and in-patient services with specific focus on emergency stabilisation, ENT, IYCF, MHPSS, GBV maternal and neonatal, maintenance of IPC. Infection prevention and control, counselling and referral and improved accessibility will be provided through the health post. Medicines will be provided free of cost to the patients. The major activities included (i) Regular Out-Patient Department (OPD) including ENT services (ii) Referral pathways (iii) Repair and maintenance of the health post (iv) Participatory Review and Reflection (iv) Door-to-door outreach (v) Distribute dignity kit items to women (vi) Conduct regular session on health, hygiene, and protection issues</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This localised intervention is focused on the continuation of rapid healthcare service provision which has proved crucial to minimising loss of life for Rohingya and Host communities with protection mainstreaming. Informed by learning from three years of adaptive programming, this intervention leverages established infrastructure, knowledge and approached attuned to the inclusive needs of Rohingya and host communities.</narrative>
  </description>
